    "body": "```\r\n[user@work tmp]$ xxd -c 6 receipts.cidx | tail\r\n024f1692: 0008 1b1e f64a  .....J\r\n024f1698: 0008 1b1f 1771  .....q\r\n024f169e: 0008 1b1f 20db  .... .\r\n024f16a4: 0008 1b1f 3fcd  ....?.\r\n024f16aa: 0008 1b1f 4371  ....Cq\r\n024f16b0: 0008 1b1f 61e3  ....a.\r\n024f16b6: 0008 1b1f 7238  ....r8\r\n024f16bc: 0008 1b1f 9dc8  ......\r\n024f16c2: 0008 1b1f b828  .....(\r\n024f16c8: 0008 1b1f dd02  ......\r\n```\r\nThe receipts have entries up to `0008.cdat`. If my math is corect, that's `6456268` entries. \r\nThe bodies and headers, however, looks strange: \r\n```\r\n[user@work tmp]$ xxd -c 6 headers.cidx | tail\r\n024f1692: 0000 0000 0000  ......\r\n024f1698: 0000 0000 0000  ......\r\n024f169e: 0000 0000 0000  ......\r\n024f16a4: 0000 0000 0000  ......\r\n024f16aa: 0000 0000 0000  ......\r\n024f16b0: 0000 0000 0000  ......\r\n024f16b6: 0000 0000 0000  ......\r\n024f16bc: 0000 0000 0000  ......\r\n024f16c2: 0000 0000 0000  ......\r\n024f16c8: 0000 0000 0000  ......\r\n```\r\nThey have as many items, but it's all empty space in them. The first item is all zeroes (as expected) then there is data, then \r\n```\r\n00000000: 0000 0000 0000  ......\r\n...\r\n024f151e: 0000 0000 0000  ......\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
